In October 2018, a final court order was entered approving the terms of a settlement in connection with the SEC’s legal
actions relating to Elon Musk’s prior consideration during the third quarter of 2018 of a take-private proposal for Tesla.
Consequently, we recognized settlement and legal expenses of $30.1 million in the year ended December 31, 2018. These expenses
were substantially paid by the end of 2018.
There were no restructuring actions in the years ended December 31, 2017 and 2016.
